 new venues of visible consumption in the urban developing world.
 Here, the basket of visible and industrial consumption has expanded, a
 new spirit of individual consumerism has replaced the rural contractual
 arrangements left untouched by successive nationalist governments.
 Looking at Tanzania, the spending on marriage and funerals seems high,
